---
import BaseLayout from '@/layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Devforge | Ray Weiss"
  description="Devforge. A game dev terminal that knows your project cold. A mode-based UI wrapping Claude Code for solo and indie game developers."
>
  <main class="px-6 py-24 lg:px-16">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl">
      <h1
        class="font-sans text-4xl font-medium tracking-tight text-foreground lg:text-5xl"
      >
        Devforge
      </h1>
      <p class="mt-6 font-serif text-lg text-muted">
        A game dev terminal that knows your project cold.
      </p>

      <div class="prose-body terminal-section mt-16">
        <p>
          Built for people who don't touch git and don't want to learn.
        </p>

        <h2>What it does</h2>

        <p>
          <strong>Your GDD stays loaded.</strong> Claude reads it before every
          session.
        </p>
        <p>
          <strong>Nothing gets lost.</strong> Session notes, tasks, and rules
          ship with each prompt.
        </p>
        <p>
          <strong>Claude learns your rules.</strong> Devforge extracts
          conventions and gotchas after each session.
        </p>
        <p>
          <strong>Watch Claude work.</strong> Live activity feed with a
          thinking-display toggle.
        </p>

        <h2>16 modes, 16 jobs</h2>

        <p>
          Each mode locks Claude to one job. Discuss talks design. Implement
          writes code. Pitch stress-tests your scope. Mod builds mods.
          Package handles distribution.
        </p>

        <ul>
          <li>Forge</li>
          <li>GDD</li>
          <li>Pitch</li>
          <li>Discuss</li>
          <li>Implement</li>
          <li>Debug</li>
          <li>Research</li>
          <li>QA</li>
          <li>Freeform</li>
          <li>Marketing</li>
          <li>Instruct</li>
          <li>Test</li>
          <li>Security</li>
          <li>UI/UX</li>
          <li>Mod</li>
          <li>Package</li>
        </ul>

        <p>
          <strong>Analog Mode</strong> toggles the whole set into tabletop
          design.
        </p>

        <h2>Try it</h2>

        <p>
          Marketing site at <a href="https://usedevforge.com"
            >usedevforge.com</a
          >. $9 on <a href="https://conflict-simulations-llc.itch.io/devforge"
            >itch</a
          >. Published under <a href="/conflict-simulations-llc"
            >Conflict Simulations LLC</a
          >.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </main>
</BaseLayout>
